title: Israel plans to evacuate Rafah, full of refugees, and attack Hamas
description: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has called for a “massive operation” in Rafah. National Security Council spokesman John Kirby warned that would be a “disaster” and that the United States “would not support it.”

title: Would you weigh yourself before boarding a plane? This airline is trying it.
description: Finnair is asking passengers to be weighed along with their carry-on baggage before boarding flights in Helsinki to improve aircraft balance calculations.

title: Pakistan stunned as ex-premier Khan’s party overperforms in election
description: Preliminary results of Thursday’s vote point to lingering support for Khan’s Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf party, which was politically sidelined after Khan ran afoul of the military.

title: Prince Harry settles phone hacking lawsuit against Mirror Group
description: The publisher agreed to a “substantial” payment on top of court-ordered damages in the precedent-setting case.

title: Which dog breeds live the longest? Take our quiz
description: According to a new study, the median life expectancy of all dogs is about 12.5 years — but when it comes to longevity, which breed is top dog?

title: The journalists killed in Gaza — and what they tried to show the world
description: At least 78 journalists and media workers have been killed over four months of war in Gaza, according to the Committee to Protect Journalists.

title: Seiji Ozawa, groundbreaking Japanese conductor, dies at 88
description: In the 1970s, at the Boston Symphony Orchestra, his studiously hip, turtle-necked, love-beaded image made him seem a new sort of music director for a new age.

title: Iranian armed with ax and knife takes hostages on train, shot dead
description: The ordeal on the train lasted for four hours before police stormed the train and shot the hostage-taker dead.

title: Thai haven draws Chinese tech bros, moms and stoners seeking freedom
description: As freedoms have steadily eroded in China, an increasing number of Chinese are finding intellectual and political refuge in the backpacker town of Chiang Mai.

title: Texas A&M to close Qatar campus, citing regional instability
description: The decision comes as the war in Gaza has escalated tensions across the Middle East, and follows increased criticism of Qatar specifically for its ties to Hamas.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Biden calls Israel’s conduct in Gaza ‘over the top’ in rare rebuke
description: The president’s comments followed criticism from U.S. officials in recent days about civilian deaths and a spiraling humanitarian disaster in Gaza.

title: Netanyahu’s delusional, deadly quest for ‘total victory’
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu claimed that “total victory” over Hamas was “within touching distance” and promised the “eternal disarmament of Gaza.”

title: Putin, in rambling interview, barely lets Tucker Carlson get a word in
description: The Russian president appeared to choose to speak to the former Fox News host because of his perceived influence in the Republican Party in an election year.

title: Mapping the ongoing eruptions in Iceland
description: Over the past three years, the Reykjanes Peninsula of Iceland has been experiencing eruptive lava events that continue to move closer to vital infrastructure and the town of Grindavik.
